# Dijkstra's Algorithm

## Problem
Find the shortest path from a source vertex to all other vertices.

## Approach
1. Initialize distances as infinity
2. Set source distance to 0
3. Pick minimum distance vertex
4. Update distances of adjacent vertices
5. Repeat until all vertices are processed

## Time Complexity
- O(V^2)

## Space Complexity
- O(V)

## Example Output
Vertex   Distance
0        0
1        10
2        50
3        30
4        60